The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, May 06, 2004 				 Dabur pays 200% dividend
 OUR CORRESPONDENT 																								New Delhi, May 5: Dabur India Limited has announced a 200 per cent dividend for fiscal 2003-04. This is the highest-ever payout by the FMCG major.																								Daburs annual net profit surged by 40.6 per cent to Rs 101.20 crore, during the fiscal. Sales rose 9.5 per cent to Rs 1,147.98 crore. 																								The board is happy to further step up its dividend payout during the year and announce its highest ever dividend so far to reward its investors and shareholders This is the highest dividend declared by the company till date, said V. C. Burman, chairman of Dabur India Ltd.																								The Dabur board decided to declare 140 per cent final dividend to its shareholders at a meeting held here today. With this announcement, the total dividend paid this year would go up to 200 per cent, which includes the interim dividend of 60 per cent announced by the company in September last year. 																								The consolidated net profit of the company was up 36.8 per cent at Rs 109.32 crore, sales up by 12 per cent to Rs 1,329.6 crore during the year. The consolidated results include Dabur India and its relevant subsidiaries. 																								For Dabur, the total outgo on account of dividend payout this year has increased 56.57 per cent to Rs 57.25 crore, up from Rs 40.07 crore last year. 
